author: Robert Burns and Lolita C. Baldor, Associated Press
title: Russia, US agree on Syria; Iraqis won't seek Russian strikes
text: Photo: Alexander Kots, AP FILE - In this Oct. 3, 2015, file photo, a Russian SU-24M jet fighter armed with laser guided bombs takes off from a runaway at Hmeimim airbase in Syria. Russia and the United States signed an agreement Oct. 20 designed to minimize the risk of collisions and other dangers as both countries carry out airstrikes in Syria. (Alexander Kots, Komsomolskaya Pravda, Photo via AP) FILE - In this Oct. 3, 2015, file photo, a Russian SU-24M jet... WASHINGTON (AP) — The U.S. and Russia on Tuesday put into practice new rules designed to minimize the risk of air collisions between military aircraft over Syria, while Iraqi leaders pledged they would not invite Russian airpower over their nation.
